According to a survey conducted by the UK Commission for Employment and Skills in 2014, 17 per cent of the reasons that employers mentioned problems in the occupation of vacancies were related to a lack of language skills.
Therefore, language skills are increasingly required when it comes to preparing young people for their future occupation.
As more and more open jobs require languages, these skills are essential in a globalized world.
Regardless of the profession chosen, young people who have learned a second language will have a real advantage in the future through such a lifelong ability.
To be able to communicate directly with people from other countries, multilingual people will automatically give a lead to competitors.
According to a YouGov survey of more than 4,000 adults in the United Kingdom in 2013, 75 percent could not speak a foreign language well enough to entertain, and French was spoken as the only language of a two-digit percentage (15 percent).
