Children who speak several languages, in particular languages of developing countries, will have better opportunities to find meaningful employment.
In Scotland, different languages are taught at all schools.
A number of schools will focus on the more classic modern languages, while other languages will be taught that are considered to be the most important for the United Kingdom in terms of 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Wherever your child’s interests lie, independent schools will always be able to choose a number of languages with appropriately specialised teachers.
Scottish independent schools are committed to creating a learning environment that prepares the children and equips them with the skills necessary for their success, whatever the future holds.
At this stage, in a global economic environment, it cannot be denied that languages remain of fundamental importance for the future of the country, and that is why this needs to be reflected in education.
In fact, modern languages should be regarded as 'international communication capability'.
Independent schools will continue to offer young people in Scotland this choice, diversity and excellence.
